12 The Department shall:
13 (1) provide each individual who is released from a correctional facility with
14 a voter registration application and documentation with the individual’s discharge papers
15 that informs the individual that the individual’s voting rights have been restored;
16 (2) display a sign in each parole and probation office, in a conspicuous
17 location where notices to the public are customarily posted, indicating that any individual
18 who is no longer incarcerated has the right to vote; and
19 (3) post a notice, in a conspicuous location on the Department’s website,
20 indicating that any individual who is no longer incarcerated has the right to vote.
